Salary: $2800 - $3500 per month
Location: Central
Job Description:
- Demonstrate a high standard of patient care by performing clinical nursing procedures that meet the patients’ immediate physical and emotional needs
- Monitor patients’ conditions before procedures
- Administering medication
- Educating patients throughout procedures
- Maintaining instruments and equipment for procedures
- Assist doctors with treatments/clinical procedures/day cases as required in accordance with established hospital policies, procedures and guidelines.
- Any other ad-hoc duties when necessary
Requirement:
- State Registered Nurse with at least 1-2 year of relevant experience
- Minimum Nitec or Diploma in Nursing or equivalent
- Good interpersonal and communication skills
- Bilingual in English and Mandarin to liaise with Mandarin or English-speaking patients
- Compassionate, positive and caring nature Meticulous and accurate.
